🐳 Running the Project (Docker - Recommended)

Requirements

Docker Desktop (Windows/Mac) or Docker Engine (Linux)

WSL enabled (Windows users only)

Run the application

docker compose up --build

🌐 Access

Frontend:
http://localhost:5173

Backend:
http://localhost:8000

⚙️ What happens automatically

MySQL container starts

Backend waits for the database to be ready

.env is created if missing

Laravel APP_KEY is generated

Database migrations are executed

Seed data is inserted

Backend API starts

Frontend application starts

💻 Running Without Docker

Requirements

PHP 8.2+

Composer

Node.js 18+

MySQL

Backend

cd backend

composer install

cp .env.example .env

php artisan key:generate

Configure database in .env

DB_CONNECTION=mysql
DB_HOST=127.0.0.1
DB_PORT=3306
DB_DATABASE=rockencantech
DB_USERNAME=root
DB_PASSWORD=your_password

Run migrations and seed

php artisan migrate --seed

Start backend

php artisan serve

Backend URL:
http://127.0.0.1:8000

Frontend

cd frontend

npm install

npm run dev

Frontend URL:
http://localhost:5173

🐧 Running on Linux (Ubuntu)

Install dependencies

sudo apt update

PHP + extensions

sudo apt install php php-cli php-mbstring php-xml php-mysql unzip curl

Composer

curl -sS https://getcomposer.org/installer
 | php
sudo mv composer.phar /usr/local/bin/composer

Node.js via NVM

curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh
 | bash

(restart terminal)

nvm install 20
nvm use 20

MySQL

sudo apt install mysql-server

Configure MySQL

sudo mysql

CREATE DATABASE rockencantech;

Run project

Follow the steps from:
Running Without Docker

🔐 Authentication

The application uses Laravel Sanctum.

After login or registration:

Token is stored in localStorage

Requests include:

Authorization: Bearer {token}

📡 API Endpoints

Public Routes

GET /api/products

GET /api/products/{id}

GET /api/categories

GET /api/products?category={id}

GET /api/products?search={query}

POST /api/register

POST /api/login

Protected Routes

POST /api/products

PUT /api/products/{id}

DELETE /api/products/{id}

🧠 Architecture

Backend

Service Layer handles business logic

Repository Pattern handles database operations

Controllers remain clean and focused

Resources and Collections standardize API responses

Frontend

Pages represent application screens

Components are reusable UI elements

API layer centralizes HTTP requests

Types provide strong typing with TypeScript

🧪 Seed Data

The application includes seed data for testing:

Categories:

Electronics

Books

Home

Clothing

Products are automatically generated during migration.

